<subSubSection id="0A66C1E0B4C8FDF123DF938DF99EC1E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="06557A6FC92575E0767066C45FF32422" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="61E1E065D2D7ACF908B359945813A8E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
Differing from var. 
<taxonomicName id="DDA75E1BCE252E7A08C02FB963F27A98" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium longiflorum var. brownii" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="longiflorum" variety="brownii">Lilium longiflorum brownii</taxonomicName>
by the greenish colouration on the outside of the corolla. 
<taxonomicName id="09F4384D0766D2202680A02C4BD5816C" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium wenshanense" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis id="E84651F75DA13419B79F3AC623945E23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Lilium wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was differentiated by having articulated scales, a feature now found to vary across the range of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="08989CEE25F1B1EDA30949592945E160" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4A449652B07269013DCF26C86E00042B" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE2D1B8CA8CC05852674BB71F931C426" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="8CB461647FB631230502B484964F7B45" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">China</emphasis>
: Anhui, Fujian, Gansu, Guangdong, Guangxi, Guizhou, Henan, Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Shaanxi, Sichuan, Yunnan, Zhejiang.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1A1DE53D55CEDBAC265E4F295ABB6E5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="8E1D45D1DF29E3710283D2CF14DB12A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E84E27C33F22293386D6992A96D3F8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Growing in open grassy meadows, rocky hillsides, open woods and amongst low scrub, 100 to 2200 m alt. Flowering in June to August.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
